---
import { ViewTransitions } from 'astro:transitions';
import HomeLayout from '../layouts/HomeLayout.astro';
---

<script>
	let stat1Num = document.querySelector('.stat1 .num');
	let stat3Num = document.querySelector('.stat3 .num');
	let interval = 1000;

	const animateNumber = (
		numElement: HTMLElement,
		startValue: number,
		endValue: number,
		increment: number,
	) => {
		let duration = Math.floor(interval / endValue);
		let counter = setInterval(() => {
			startValue += increment;
			numElement.textContent = numElement.closest('.stat1')
				? `${startValue.toFixed(0)}%.`
				: startValue.toFixed(1);
			if (startValue >= endValue) clearInterval(counter);
		}, duration);
	};

	const observerStat1 = new IntersectionObserver(
		entries => {
			const entry = entries[0]; // access the first (and only) entry directly
			if (entry.isIntersecting) {
				animateNumber(stat1Num as HTMLElement, 0, 73, 1);
				observerStat1.unobserve(entry.target); // stop observing after animation starts
			}
		},
		{
			threshold: 1, // animation starts once 100% of element's visible
			rootMargin: '50px', // animation starts 50px before element's visible
		},
	);

	const observerStat3 = new IntersectionObserver(
		entries => {
			const entry = entries[0];
			if (entry.isIntersecting) {
				animateNumber(stat3Num as HTMLElement, 0, 73.5, 3.5);
				observerStat3.unobserve(entry.target);
			}
		},
		{
			threshold: 1,
			rootMargin: '100px',
		},
	);

	observerStat1.observe(stat1Num as HTMLElement);
	observerStat3.observe(stat3Num as HTMLElement);
</script>

<HomeLayout title="BovEco - iGEM 2024">
	<ViewTransitions />
	<main>
		<div class="welcome-text">
			<img
				src="/waterloo/img/waterloo-igem-pixelated.png"
				alt="Waterloo iGEM Logo"
			/>
			<h3>Waterloo iGEM Presents...</h3>
			<h1 transition:animate="fade">BovEco</h1>
			<h2>
				Fighting <span>climate change</span>, one cow at a <span>time!</span>
			</h2>
		</div>
		<div class="stat1">
			<div class="num"></div>
			<div class="text">
				That's the proportion of agricultural <span>methane</span>
				emissions released by ruminants.
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="stat2">
			<span>
				<b>One</b> cow produces over <b>100</b> kg of methane a year...
			</span>
			<img src="img/cows/burping-cow.gif" alt="Burping Cow" />
			<img src="img/cliff-edge.png" alt="Cliff Edge" />
			<img src="img/cliff-column.png" alt="Cliff Column" />
			<span>
				...now imagine close to <br /><b>1.5 billion</b> cows globally.
			</span>
		</div>
		<div class="stat3">
			that is
			<div class="num"></div>
			<div class="text">
				million metric tons of enteric methane produced by cattleâ€”globally.
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="fact1">
			<div>As the global population increases,</div>
			<div>so will the demand for beef and dairy products.</div>
		</div>
		<div class="fact2">
			<p>Methane emissions drive serious environmental issues:</p>
			<p>
				accelerating global temperatures, dragrading air quality, and
				threatening crop growth--all of which impact human and animal health.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="fact3">
			Addressing these CH4 issues is crucial for a healthier planet.
		</div>
		<div class="rationale">
			<div>So why tackle CH4?</div>
			<img src="" alt="" />
			<div>
				Methane has a shorter atmospheric life of 7-12 years compared to other
				long-lasting GHGs.
			</div>
			<div>
				Reducing methane emissions can lead to quicker reductions in global
				warming and atmospheric GHG levels.
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="proposal">
			<div>So what if...</div>
			<div>GMO plants used to feed cows could be modified to</div>
			<div>solve methane problem?</div>
		</div>
		<div class="bottom">
			<!-- <img src="img/ocean.png" alt="" /> -->
		</div>
	</main>
</HomeLayout>

